column5: Have a nice house to live in, in a good heighbourhood. Regretably, the landlord and the neighbouring bakery are having a pissing match. Next thing I know neighbour has involved the town, and the town now wants the back quarter of the house torn down or a new foundation built. Either way we get put out the door.  At least I have a good 3 months to find another decent home.
Man that stinks, I hate moving
Sorry to hear that...hope you fine something really good for a new place
Sorry to hear that Bruce, hope the next place is better.
Sorry to hear of your luck Bruce.  Good luck as you go home hunting.
That sucks my friend. Keep your eyes open and keep putting out the word and something good will come up. Your due for a good break.
Boy you just can't catch a break can you? At least you have time to do some looking! Kawarthas maybe?
I'd move further north in a heartbeat. Sadly I'm outvoted 3 to 1 by my family
Brutal  Good luck in looking bruce!  Hopefully youse find a gem!
I'd move further north in a heartbeat. Sadly I'm outvoted 3 to 1 by my family Geez...thats too bad...you would love it here

I'd move north, quicker than a heart beat!  But 2 daughters & 3 grandchildren keep me in Niagara.  I keep telling my wife we 'd only be 4 or 5 hour drive from them.  She could visit them every week end, while I go fishing!  LOL!
Moved up here from downtown Toronto when I was 15 because my dad got a job on a long construction project. I can't think of any place I would rather live.
